'''裸體派對'''是要求參與者[[裸体|裸体]]參加的[[派對|派對]]。此活動主要和大學校園有關，多半也是大學生參與。裸體派對是在[[布朗大学|布朗大学]]及[[耶鲁大学|耶鲁大学]]組織類似活動之後，開始有知名度<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nysun.com/article/23347 |title=At Columbia, an Invitation to a Night of Nakedness |first=Jacob |last=Gershman |date=2005-11-22 |access-date=2008-09-05 |work=New York Sun |archive-date=2008-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724035425/http://www.nysun.com/article/23347 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。裸體派對的起源可以追溯到[[天然主義|天然主義]]運動以及校園[[露體癖|露體癖]]，不過現在的裸體派對是從1980年代從[[布朗大学|布朗大学]]開始的<ref name="nyt-070107"/>。裸體派對的參與者表示他們在進入派對時都已是裸體的，每個人不論其體型如何，也都允許裸體，幾分鐘後就不覺得尷尬了<ref>{{cite news |url=http://orient.bowdoin.edu/orient/article.php?section=3&date=2006-12-01&id=5 |title=Naked parties: an expose |work=The Bowdoin Orient College Paper |location=Brunswick, Maine |date=2006-12-01 |access-date=2008-09-05 |last=Abbruzzese |first=Kelsey |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081007060105/http://orient.bowdoin.edu/orient/article.php?section=3&date=2006-12-01&id=5 |archive-date=2008-10-07 |dead-url=no }} (dead link 10 February 2020)</ref>。根據報導的資料，大部份的裸體派對不會限制性別<ref>{{cite news |url=http://cbs3.com/specialreports/College.Party.Naked.2.307373.html |first=Angela |last=Russell |title=Naked College Parties |date=2007-02-13 |work=CBS3 |publisher=CBS Broadcasting, Inc. |access-date=2008-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080822085757/http://cbs3.com/specialreports/College.Party.Naked.2.307373.html |archive-date=2008-08-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。在體派對中，裸體「比較是社交互動的體驗，不是性體驗。」<ref name="nyt-070107">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/07/education/edlife/07nakedparties.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all&oref=slogin |title=Black Tie Optional |first=Rachel |last=Aviv |work=New York Times |date=2007-01-07 |access-date=2008-09-05 |archive-date=2021-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208123056/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/07/education/edlife/07nakedparties.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all&oref=slogin |dead-url=no }}</ref>

裸體派對的興起也帶來國際性的爭議。有些學生不希望其學校和這類的活動有關。這類的關注也出現在許多的文學作品中，例如[[汤姆·沃尔夫|汤姆·沃尔夫]]的《{{le|我是夏綠蒂·賽門斯|I Am Charlotte Simmons}}》（I Am Charlotte Simmons）、纳塔利·克林斯基（Natalie Krinsky）的《搞上耶魯》（Chloe Does Yale）<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/arts/main.jhtml?xml=/arts/2006/03/02/ftyale02.xml |work=Telegraph UK |title=Naked parties... very odd, unnatural |publisher=Telegraph Media Group |date=2006-02-03 |access-date=2008-09-05 |first=Catherine |last=Elsworth |archive-date=2008-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080506080249/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/arts/main.jhtml?xml=%2Farts%2F2006%2F03%2F02%2Fftyale02.xml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。宗教團體試圖禁止在都市中的裸體派對<ref name="bbc-021001">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/2289466.stm | title=Call to ban 'naked' party | publisher=BBC News | date=1 October 2002 | accessdate=2021-02-26 | archive-date=2004-07-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040707122243/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/2289466.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[今日基督教|今日基督教]]》有一個標題為What to Say at a Naked Party的專欄文章，提出了和性侵犯及客觀道德等議題的關注<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2005/002/14.48.html |work=Christianity Today Magazine |publisher=Christianity Today International |title=What to Say at a Naked Party |first=Frederica |last=Mathewes-Green |date=2005-01-21 |access-date=2008-09-05 |archive-date=2008-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204205618/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2005/002/14.48.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

